com.radiantlogic.iddm.base

Interface DataProvider<OUT extends SearchResponse & HasStatus>

  • All Superinterfaces:
    Response, SearchResponse
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SequentialDataProvider<OUT>

    public interface DataProvider<OUT extends SearchResponse & HasStatus>
extends SearchResponse
    This interface defines methods for providing responses partial data.

    The interface is typically used to create a delegate that can be returned to IDDM (from a Connector or TypeConverter) then used to incrementally retrieve data from the third-party data source, instead of returning all the data at once.

    To use, the developer needs to create a class that implements this interface and each of its methods (as no default implementations are provided). The OUT type parameter specifies the response type returned from the provider to IDDM when more data is requested (for example, an LdapResponse).

    It is strongly recommended (but not required) that developers use an existing implementation, such as SequentialDataProvider, instead of directly implementing this interface.

    • Method Detail

      • isValid

        boolean isValid()
        Returns true if the provider is able to provide data.
        Returns:
        true if the provider is valid and can be queried for additional data, even if there is no more data to return. false if the provider is invalid, even if there is more data to return.

      • invalidate

        void invalidate()
        Shutdown the provider, making it unavailable for querying additional information. Cleanup open resources used by the provider in this method.
